    "content": "Marty, thank you for the clear decisions. I've updated the glossary:\n\n- **Todo title max length**: Changed from 200 to **300 characters** in `docs/glossary.md`. Aligned with your reasoning -- generous enough for real-world titles, short enough to prevent misuse as a notes field.\n\n- **Uncomplete/toggle**: Confirmed in scope for US-6. The glossary already has `uncomplete_todo()` and the bidirectional state machine. The mob is aware.\n\n- **Empty state**: Understood -- \"No todos yet\" with the add input always visible. The domain model supports this naturally (empty collection renders empty state). The visual treatment is the design team's call.\n\nAll three decisions are now reflected in the glossary. The domain model is fully aligned with the product vision.\n\nOne note: the glossary file has uncommitted changes now (the 200->300 update). I'll make sure this gets committed. Following the \"commit early\" principle."
  }
